                <ui:BuildDataTable DataTable="[dtGCC]" DisplayName="Build Data Table" sap:VirtualizedContainerService.HintSize="544,58.6666666666667" sap2010:WorkflowViewState.IdRef="BuildDataTable_1" TableInfo="&lt;NewDataSet&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;xs:schema id=&quot;NewDataSet&quot; xmlns=&quot;&quot; xmlns:xs=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema&quot; xmlns:msdata=&quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:xml-msdata&quot;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;xs:element name=&quot;NewDataSet&quot; msdata:IsDataSet=&quot;true&quot; msdata:MainDataTable=&quot;TableName&quot; msdata:UseCurrentLocale=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;      &lt;xs:complexType&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;xs:choice minOccurs=&quot;0&quot; maxOccurs=&quot;unbounded&quot;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;          &lt;xs:element name=&quot;TableName&quot;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;            &lt;xs:complexType&gt;&#xD;&#xA;              &lt;xs:sequence&gt;&#xD;&#xA;                &lt;xs:element name=&quot;Risk_x0020_Ref&quot; minOccurs=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;                  &lt;xs:simpleType&gt;&#xD;&#xA;                    &lt;xs:restriction base=&quot;xs:string&quot;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;                      &lt;xs:maxLength value=&quot;100&quot; /&gt;&#xD;&#xA;                    &lt;/xs:restriction&gt;&#xD;&#xA;                  &lt;/xs:simpleType&gt;&#xD;&#xA;                &lt;/xs:element&gt;&#xD;&#xA;                &lt;xs:element name=&quot;Risk_x0020_Name&quot; type=&quot;xs:string&quot; minOccurs=&quot;0&quot; /&gt;&#xD;&#xA;                &lt;xs:element name=&quot;Risk_x0020_Description&quot; type=&quot;xs:string&quot; minOccurs=&quot;0&quot; /&gt;&#xD;&#xA;                &lt;xs:element name=&quot;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&quot; type=&quot;xs:string&quot; minOccurs=&quot;0&quot; /&gt;&#xD;&#xA;                &lt;xs:element name=&quot;Control_x0020_Ref&quot; type=&quot;xs:string&quot; minOccurs=&quot;0&quot; /&gt;&#xD;&#xA;                &lt;xs:element name=&quot;Control_x0020_Owner&quot; type=&quot;xs:string&quot; minOccurs=&quot;0&quot; /&gt;&#xD;&#xA;                &lt;xs:element name=&quot;Control_x0020_Objective&quot; type=&quot;xs:string&quot; minOccurs=&quot;0&quot; /&gt;&#xD;&#xA;                &lt;xs:element name=&quot;Observed_x0020_Control_x0020_Activity&quot; type=&quot;xs:string&quot; minOccurs=&quot;0&quot; /&gt;&#xD;&#xA;                &lt;xs:element name=&quot;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&quot; type=&quot;xs:string&quot; minOccurs=&quot;0&quot; /&gt;&#xD;&#xA;                &lt;xs:element name=&quot;Test_x0020_Results&quot; type=&quot;xs:string&quot; minOccurs=&quot;0&quot; /&gt;&#xD;&#xA;              &lt;/xs:sequence&gt;&#xD;&#xA;            &lt;/xs:complexType&gt;&#xD;&#xA;          &lt;/xs:element&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;/xs:choice&gt;&#xD;&#xA;      &lt;/xs:complexType&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/xs:element&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/xs:schema&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;1. System Security&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;A. 1&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Policies and procedures may not have been created and communicate to users to prevent the Inappropriate/unauthorized use or disclosure of confidential information.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 5 PO 4&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;1.1&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;An information security policy exists and has been approved by senior management.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Review information security policies and procedures to determine coverage of the following areas (as per ISO17799: Code of Practice for Information Security Management ):- Security Policy- System Access Control - Computer &amp;amp; Operations Management - System Development and Maintenance – Compliance - Security Organization - Asset (Data &amp;amp; Application) Classification and Control 2. Determine that policies and procedures are up-to-date (reviewed annually and updates performed as applicable). 3. Determine that the information security policy has been approved by an appropriate level of executive management. 4. Determine that the security policy has been communicated to all system users.  &lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;A. 2&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;User access mechanisms may not be adequately configured to prevent the Inappropriate/unauthorized use or disclosure of confidential information.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 5&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;1.2&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;Access to in-scope application(s) requires a unique user ID and password assigned to each user.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Confirm access to the in-scope applications requires the use of a password. 2. Confirm desktop computers are required to use passwords. 3.  Obtain a list of user id’s for each in scope system and determine if user ID's are unique, and that individuals are assigned one user ID (as appropriate).&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;A. 3&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Default operating system accounts can be used to gain unauthorized or inappropriate systems access.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 5&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;1.3&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;Default application accounts are secured, disabled and/or their passwords are changed&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Confirm default accounts (if any) are disabled and not used for interactive login. 2. Confirm the usage of default accounts (if any) is limited as appropriate and that use of the accounts can be traced to an individual and is logged and monitored. 3. Verify the default passwords for such accounts have been changed.&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;A. 4&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Password controls may not be adequately configured to prevent the Inappropriate/unauthorized use or disclosure of confidential information.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 5&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;1.4&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;Users are authenticated to in-scope application(s) through passwords or other authentication mechanisms.   Password controls are implemented in accordance with leading practices (e.g., password complexity, minimum length, password history, etc.).&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Obtain a screenshot of the password and authentication settings of the in-scope system(s). 2. Review password and authentication settings and verify they are set in accordance with company policy and/or best practices, including the following settings: -Users are required to change their passwords upon first use - Users are prohibited from using the prior XX passwords -Passwords must be a minimum length of XX and require at least XX special characters and XX numbers -Users are required to change passwords every XX days  -Accounts are locked after XX invalid logon attempts -Locked accounts must be unlocked by an administrator&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;A. 5&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Individuals are granted access in accordance with job responsibilities and are appropriately approved.  &lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 5&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;1.5&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;IT operating procedures exist to govern the addition and modification of user access to in-scope application(s).  Specifically, access is granted based on business need and segregation of duties, and requires appropriate management approval.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Obtain the policy or procedures which govern the addition and modification of user accounts. 2. Perform a walkthrough of new user access process and verify it is in accordance with company policy. 3. Select a sample of newly added and/or modified users and obtain the related access request forms (or similar). 4. Confirm the user access provisioning policy and/or procedures were followed for sample users with new or modified access. 5. Confirm the sample access request forms were appropriately approved, and that access was granted based on business need.&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;A. 6&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Access for contractors and temporary employees is not removed in accordance with support dates.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 5&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;1.6&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;Policies and procedures are documented to address the security risks associated with temporary employee or contractor accounts.  &lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Obtain relevant policies and procedures related to the naming, tacking, and approval process for temporary employee or contractor accounts. 2. Determine if the policies adequately address relevant security concerns with these types of accounts such as mandatory periodic re-accreditation processes, limited access to client systems, and account expiration. 3. Verify that additional approval is required to change account permissions. 4. Obtain a sample set of user accounts and verify that non-employee accounts follow the defined naming convention, are readily identifiable and configured to expire after a set time period (if applicable).&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;A. 7&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Terminated employees’ accounts may be used following their termination date to access confidential information. &lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 5&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;1.7&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;Employee access to in-scope application(s) and supporting systems is reviewed and modified accordingly and promptly upon notification of job change or employment termination.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Obtain the policy or procedures which govern changes to user accounts. 2. Select a sample of employees with job changes or that were terminated during the fiscal year. 3. Confirm the user access policy and/or procedures were followed by modifying or removing access for the selected sample according to policy for any in-scope applications and supporting servers. Note: If possible, obtain a listing of all employees terminated during the audit period and systematically compare the employee listing to the user listing to validate all  terminated employees’ access was removed.  &lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;A. 8&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;User access may not be commensurate with job responsibilities.  &lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 5&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;1.8&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;A review of user access to in-scope application(s) is conducted on a periodic basis to confirm access rights are appropriate based on job roles and responsibilities.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Obtain a copy of the most recent user access review. 2. Confirm the user access review included all in-scope applications / systems. 3. Confirm the access review was reviewed and approved by an appropriate member of management. 4. Confirm required access changes were made. 5. Confirm the recertification included temporary employees and third parties.&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;A. 9&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Security incidents may not be detected or investigated.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 5&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;1.9&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;IT security administration monitors and logs privileged user activity for in-scope application(s) and supporting systems, and identified security violations are reported to senior management.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1.  Obtain documentation related to the monitoring of security alerts for in scope system(s) and determine if procedures are defined for gathering, analyzing, and reporting on security alerts to ensure that security issues are adequately addressed in a timely manner. 2.  Confirm that an appropriate individual is responsible for looking at audit data for each place where data resides.  Confirm that the frequency of review has been defined.  &lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;A. 10&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;System administrator accounts can be used to gain inappropriate systems access.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 5&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;1.10&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;Privileged user access to in-scope application(s) is strictly limited to those IT associates responsible for security administration.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Obtain a system generated list of all users with administrative access to the in-scope system(s). 2. Confirm privileged users are segregated from performing business functions (i.e. financial reporting) in applications.  Additionally, confirm that security personnel are not responsible for developing program code (change management) and that access is assigned in accordance with job responsibilities.&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;2. Manage the Configuration (limited scope; please utilize audit program for network security)&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;B. 1&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Infrastructure is not updated with patches to protect against vulnerabilities.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 5&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;2.1&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;In-scope application(s) and supporting systems are regularly updated with approved software patches.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Obtain any relevant patch management policies and review. 2. Confirm policies are followed and reviewed on a regular basis.&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;B. 2&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Infrastructure is not updated with virus protection to adequately protect against vulnerabilities.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 5&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;2.2&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;In-scope application(s) and supporting systems are regularly updated with approved software patches.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Confirm anti-virus software has been installed on all in-scope application servers (if Windows servers are used).&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;B. 3&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Management does not have procedures to protect Infrastructure against vulnerabilities.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 5&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;2.3&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;The organization develops and implements a security plan for the information system that provides an overview of the security requirements for the system and a description of the security controls in place or planned for meeting those requirements.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Review system security plan and determine if appropriate. 2. Determine that the system security plan is aligned with the overall IT strategic plan. 3. Determine that the system security plan is kept up to date with change in the IT environment.&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;3. Problem Management&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;C. 1&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Operational failures and security incidents and problems are not detected and acted upon. Critical issues are not acknowledged a timely or appropriate manner.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 10&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;3.1&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;Incidents are tracked and recorded in a problem management system.  The status of incidents are regularly updated and reviewed.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Obtain a copy of the Incident Management Policy and/or Problem Management policy and procedures. 2. Review the policy to validate it addresses the areas of incident detection, logging, analysis, escalation and resolution. 3. Confirm incidents are defined and are recorded in a problem management or similar system (trouble tickets).  Obtain an export of incident / problem tickets from the system. 4. Select a sample of problem tickets and confirm incidents are prioritized based on severity.&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;C. 2&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Operational failures and security incidents and problems are not detected and acted upon. Critical issues are not acknowledged a timely or appropriate manner.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;PO 4&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;3.2&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;The organization develops, disseminates and periodically reviews/updates a formal documented incident response policy and formal, documented procedures.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Determine that policies and procedures have assigned owners and are up-to-date. 2. Confirm an escalation procedure exists allowing for incidents to be routed to appropriate individuals based on need.  For a sample of incident / problem tickets, validate that issues were escalated to the appropriate personnel within required timeframes.  &lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;C. 3&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Operational failures and security incidents and problems are not detected and acted upon. Critical issues are not acknowledged a timely or appropriate manner.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 10&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;3.3&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;The organization tracks and documents information system security incidents on an ongoing basis.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Determine that incidents are tracked and monitored until resolution.  Identify if any long-outstanding incidents remain open and validate the status with management. 2. For a sample of completed incidents, determine that a root-cause analysis was performed. 3. Validate that open items are monitored and reported on an ongoing basis.  &lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;4. Change Management&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;D. 1&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Policies and procedures have not been defined and implemented to prevent unauthorized or unintended changes. &lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;AI 6&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;4.1&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;Change Management policies and procedures are in place and consider the development and acquisition of new applications and changes to existing applications.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Obtain a copy of the Change Management procedures. 2. Verify Change Management policies and procedures have been published and communicated to relevant stakeholders.&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;D. 2&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Program changes may not function according to business requirements. &lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;AI 6&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;4.2&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;Users test and approve all significant changes to applications prior to migration to production to ensure that the program modifications perform in accordance with project specifications.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Select a sample of changes from a system generated list of changes moved into production. 2. Obtain the corresponding documentation for the changes and verify they were unit, system and end-user tested prior to being moved to production. 3. Verify the appropriate approvals from IT and application/system owner personnel were obtained prior to commencing development for the change and after successful testing of the change.  &lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;D. 3&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Program changes may not function according to business requirements.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;AI 6&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;4.3&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;Implemented changes meet business requirements.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Review IT change management policies, standards, and procedures to determine whether changes of significant cost or risk require approval by business users at appropriate points. 2. Through interviews and reviews of documentation, determine that for each significant change, a post-implementation review assesses its effectiveness and measures it against the business case applied in initiating the change.&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;D. 4&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Changes that must be implemented faster than the&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;AI 6&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;4.4&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;Emergency changes are implemented in a way that preserves change controls.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Determine that IT change management policies, standards, and procedures establish parameters defining emergency changes and procedures to control these changes when they circumvent the normal process of technical, operational and management assessment prior to implementation. 2. Select a sample of emergency changes during the audit&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;D. 5&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Unauthorized or unintended changes can be made to production programs or the network.  &lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;AI 6&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;4.5&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;Access to migrate program changes into production for in-scope application(s) is restricted to authorized individuals.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;5. Computer Operations&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;E. 1&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Policies, procedures and/or guidelines addressing data center operations have not been documented, communicated and/or updated to ensure guidance reflects current business conditions&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;PO 6&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;5.1&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;The organization develops, disseminates and periodically reviews/updates a formal documented system maintenance policy and formal, documented procedures.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Review maintenance policies and procedures and determine if appropriate. 2. Determine that policies and procedures have assigned owners and are up-to-date.&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;E. 2&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Backups are not performed successfully. Data may not be available for restoration of financial statements and/or other critical transactions.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 11&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;5.2&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;Management has implemented a strategy for cyclical backup of in-scope application(s) and data as well as a tape management system that tracks where backup tapes are located.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Obtain a copy of the backup policy.  Verify the policy contains all in scope applications and supporting systems. 2. Confirm that an inventory of all backups is maintained in a system and that the process for updating the inventory is functioning properly. 3. Select a sample of backups from the inventory and ensure that the location can be identified or the final resolution of the tape is documented. 4. Select a sample of backup schedules and confirm they are configured to comply with the policy. 5. Obtain a copy of backup logs and select a sample of failed backups.  Confirm failed backups are investigated, escalated and resolved.&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;E. 3&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Backup data may not be stored in a secure location or available in the event a recovery is required.  &lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 11&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;5.3&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;Backup media is stored in a secure location (e.g., fireproof safe, offsite location).&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Confirm backup tapes are stored at a secure location. 2. Confirm the retention period for backup tapes is in accordance with business requirements.  &lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;E. 4&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Data that is backed up may not be restored.  &lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 11&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;5.4&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;Backup media of in-scope application(s) is tested periodically for successful recovery.  &lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Obtain supporting evidence backup media of in-scope application(s) is tested for successful recovery. 2. Determine if the backup location has an inventory of on-site tapes. 3. Select a sample of tapes from the list and make certain that they exist in the inventory. 4. Select a sample of tapes from the physical locations and ensure that they exist on the list. 5. Confirm failed backup restores are investigated, escalated and resolved.&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;E. 5&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;System processing and job runs do not occur or operate as intended.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 13&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;5.5&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;The organization develops, disseminates and periodically reviews/updates a formal documented batch scheduling and processing policy and formal, documented procedures.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Review batch scheduling and processing policies and procedures and determine if in-scope systems and applications are addressed. 2. Determine that policies and procedures have assigned owners and are up-to-date.&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;E. 6&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Batch jobs are scheduled and executed in accordance with business requirements. Jobs that do not complete and identified and corrected by management.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 13&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;5.6&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;The organization schedules batch processing to occur on a periodic basis in accordance with business requirements.  &lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Determine that the organization has implemented a schedule for periodic batch processing. 2. Review the process used by the organization to initiate batch processing, automatic or manual, and determine if appropriate. 3. Determine that the batch processing schedule meets the requirements of the business.  Ensure batch and job runs are approved by appropriate business &amp;amp; IT personnel. 4. Determine that the batch processing schedule and batch processing tool configuration is backed up. 5.  Correct data file versions are verified prior to execution. 6. Correct program versions are verified prior to execution. 7. Programs and data files are backed-up on a regular basis. 8. All and only programs included on the production schedule are executed. 9.  Operations personnel are alerted to job processing anomalies that may require operator intervention. 10. Non-production programs are not scheduled for execution. 11. Operator actions are logged, reviewed and approved. 12. All batch program processing, including anomalies, is logged. 13. Processing reports are generated to support user reconciliation controls.&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;E. 7&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Jobs that do not complete and identified and corrected by management.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 13&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;5.7&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;The organization monitors the status of batch processing and determines an appropriate cause of action if a failure is identified.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Review the process used by the organization for monitoring the status of batch processing and determine if appropriate. 2. Determine what process is followed if a failure is identified and assess for appropriateness. 3. Determine that a root-cause analysis is performed to identify the cause of any problems identified.&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;E. 8&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Data or processing integrity issues may not be identified and resolved.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;PO 2&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;5.8&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;An interface map or other document contains a library of all interfaces. Periodic reconciliations of in-scope application interfaces are in place.  &lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Obtain an interface map or other system documentation showing interfaces which exist within the environment. 2. Confirm the map accurately shows all interfaces and was recently updated.&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;E. 9&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Data or processing integrity issues may not be identified and resolved.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 11&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;5.9&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;Interfaces are monitored to confirm all data is accepted, processed, and expected results are received.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Determine the mechanism for monitoring in-scope application interfaces, and confirm interface errors and issues are appropriately detected, communicated, corrected, and resolved.&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;E. 10&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Data or processing integrity issues may not be identified and resolved.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 11&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;5.10&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;Contingency plans are in place for situations of interface inoperability.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Confirm contingency plans are in place for situations of interface inoperability for all in-scope application interfaces.&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;E. 11&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Key systems and applications are not within the Business Continuity/Disaster Recovery Plan.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 4&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;5.11&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;Formal Business Continuity / Disaster Recovery procedures exist and consider all in-scope application(s).&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Obtain a copy of the Business Continuity / Disaster Recovery procedures and confirm the procedures verify that in-scope applications and supporting systems have been included in the plans.  &lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;6. Physical Security&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;F. 1&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Procedures have not been defined to adequately safeguard infrastructure from physical and environmental risks.  &lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;PO 4&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;6.1&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;The organization develops, disseminates and periodically reviews/updates a formal documented physical and environmental protection policy and formal, documented. &lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Review physical and environmental protection policies and procedures and determine if procedures address the physical and environmental risks to the infrastructure. 2. Determine that policies and procedures have assigned owners and are up-to-date.&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;F. 2&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Company facilities are not physically secured.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 12&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;6.2&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;The organization develops and keeps current lists of personnel with authorized access to facilities containing information systems and issues appropriate authorization credentials.  Designated officials within the organization review and approve the access list and authorization credentials.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Obtain a list of individuals with access to the facilities and data center.  2. Review the process for authorizing users to have access to secure locations.  Select a sample of individuals with access to the facilities and data center and verify that access was approved by the appropriate personnel and is commensurate with job responsibilities.  3. Validate that management has procedures in place to periodically review access to the facilities and data center.  Obtain a copy of the last review performed by management and validate that changes to physical access were implemented as required per the review.  &lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;F. 3&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Data center and Infrastructure is not adequately secured.  &lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 12&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;6.3&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;The organization controls all physical access points to facilities containing information systems and verifies individual access authorizations before granting access to facilities.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Determine that physical access to computer rooms, media libraries and IT development and operations areas is restricted to authorized personnel.&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;F. 4&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Infrastructure is not adequately protected against vulnerabilities.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 12&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;6.4&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;The organization monitors physical access to information systems to detect and respond to incidents.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Determine that the organization periodically reviews physical access to computer rooms, media libraries and IT development and operations areas.  Obtain evidence of management’s review of authorized and unauthorized attempts to the data center and verify management appropriately investigated activities.&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;F. 5&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Visitors or contractors may obtain unauthorized access to computer facilities and infrastructure.  &lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 12&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;6.5&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;The organization controls physical access to information systems by authenticating visitors before authorizing access to facilities or areas other than areas designated as publicly accessible.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Determine that visitors are vetted before they are granted access to computer rooms, tape libraries or programming areas. 2. Determine that visitors are required to sign-in and that they are escorted throughout the facilities. 3. Determine that the organization periodically reviews the visitor access log.&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;F. 6&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Computer systems may not be available due to power loss.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 12&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;6.6&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;The organization provides a short-term uninterruptible power supply to facilitate an orderly shutdown of the information system in the event of a primary power source loss.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Determine that uninterruptible power supplies, generators and other devices are maintained and tested on a periodic basis. 2. Determine that the uninterruptible power supply is adequate for the organization. 3. Determine that IT personnel are alerted to power disruptions.&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;F. 7&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Infrastructure is not adequately protected against fire vulnerabilities.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 12&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;6.7&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;The organization employs and maintains fire suppression and detection devices/systems that can be activated in the event of a fire.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Determine that smoke and/or heat detectors are located below the raised floor and on the ceiling in the computer room. 2. Determine that fire extinguishers and fire suppression devices are installed in the computer room. 3. Determine that sprinklers, extinguishers, gas suppression, alarms and other fire protection devices are maintained and tested on a regular basis. 4. Determine that IT personnel (including those in the data center) are alerted to fires. 5. Determine that an evacuation plan is in place for data centers in places in the event of a gas release.&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;F. 8&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Infrastructure is not adequately protected against temperature vulnerabilities.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 12&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;6.8&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;The organization regularly maintains within acceptable levels and monitors the temperatures and humidity within facilities containing information systems.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Determine that temperature and humidity devices (including air conditioning) are installed in the computer room. 2. Determine that temperature and humidity devices are maintained and tested on a regular basis. 3. Determine that IT personnel are alerted to temperature issues.&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;F. 9&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Infrastructure is not adequately protected against water vulnerabilities.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 12&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;6.9&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;The organization protects the information system from water damage resulting from broken plumbing lines or other sources of water leakage by ensuring that master shutoff valves are accessible, working properly and known to key personnel.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Determine that the floor in the computer room is raised. 2. Determine that IT personnel are alerted to water issues.&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;F. 10&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Infrastructure is not adequately protected against vulnerabilities.&lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 12&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;6.10&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;The organization locates computer rooms in suitable locations.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Determine that computer rooms are not located in areas that are exposed to threats such as electrical interference, significant heat, vibrations, etc.&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;F. 11&lt;/Risk_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Risk_x0020_Description&gt;Individuals may gain unauthorized access to confidential information.  &lt;/Risk_x0020_Description&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;DS 12&lt;/COBIT_x0020_Domain_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Ref&gt;6.11&lt;/Control_x0020_Ref&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Control_x0020_Objective&gt;The organization restricts the ability for personnel to extract data from information systems using USB thumb drives, iPods, mobile phones and other devices.&lt;/Control_x0020_Objective&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;1. Determine that the organization has locked down its computer systems, restricting the connection of portable devices such as mobile phones and USB thumb drives.&lt;/Audit_x0020_Step_x0020_To_x0020_Be_x0020_Completed&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/TableName&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/NewDataSet&gt;" />
